statement.p:
A function f(x) has a local maximum at a point x=c in the domain
if there is an interval (a,b) with c \in (a,b)
so that f(x) \le f(c) for all x \in (a,b).

A function f(x) has a local minimum at a point x=c in the domain
if there is an interval (a,b) with c \in (a,b)
so that f(c) \le f(x) for all x \in (a,b).

